This memorandum, issued by President Barack Obama on September 12, 2011, delegates the function conferred upon the President by section 2(a) of the Special Agent Samuel Hicks Families of Fallen Heroes Act to the Administrator of General Services. The Act, also known as Public Law 111-178, aims to support the families of fallen heroes. The President delegates the authority to the Administrator to prescribe the applicable regulations and directs them to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.